{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Amend Human Rights Act and review all laws",
        "additional_details": "We think laws used to be based on actions but are now too much based on feelings and words, which we believe is eroding our rights. We believe laws based on feelings are a very bad idea, because of their subjective nature, and that such laws can be weaponised. \r\nWe consider that amongst the UK population this has generated great fear of saying or doing the wrong thing, and that, furthermore, our Police are wasting time policing feelings and words as opposed to tackling other crime. Free speech is necessary for a healthy democracy.",
        "background": "We would like the Human Rights Act 1998 to be amended to cover \u201cfreedom of speech and thought\u201d rather than \u201cfreedom of expression\u201d. We would also like all laws to be reviewed from a human rights perspective, and any laws that are assessed to breach these rights to be repealed.",
